    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="upa.00068.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey<ptr target="upa.00186_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1878-12-25" rend="right">Dec 25&#8212;p m</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>

            <p>Yours of day before yesterday <choice><abbr>rec'd</abbr><expan>received</expan></choice>&#8212;I am well as usual, &#38; bustling about&#8212;Sister and brother well&#8212;Bitter cold &#38; gusty gales here for two days<ptr target="upa.00186_n2"/>&#8212;I don't go out so much&#8212;Went over Sunday morning to foot of Arch St. Phila. to breakfast on a steamer&#8212;bountiful breakfast&#8212;jolly democratic three hours<ptr target="upa.00186_n3"/>&#8212;I have written to Miss Jenny G.&#8212;I sent John Burroughs your Brooklyn address&#8212;he &#38; wife are away spending Christmas holidays&#8212;I shall send him your present address&#8212;havn't seen E's<ptr target="upa.00186_n4"/> portrait yet&#8212;I am writing this up in my room&#8212;Sun shines out as I finish</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">W W</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p><hi rend="underline">Merry Christmas to you &amp; all</hi></p>
            </postscript>    
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="upa.00068.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
